lenders.occupational_info: I am a professional health worker and a Roman Catholic Religious Brother with the FIC Brothers based in Ghana. Having studied at the undergrade and graduate levels in health has broadened by development orientation to community development work since 2003. I work passionately for people with disabilities and women and children who are the most marginalized in soceity. Been passonate about these groups means siding with them in joy and in sorrow. A recent engagement on women works is the widows association in development project in the Ullo traditional area, in the Jirarapa district of the upper west region of Ghana. Married men are dying more than the women in the traditional area. The question that came up is, if women are the bread winners whilst the men are alive, what happens when the man dies? The answer is the woman becomes a double breadwinner of the family with no job opportunities for an income. Based on the plight of these widows, the project intends to establish income generating activities that will be accessible and to be used to make an income to support their livelihood. In this way, the education of thier children will also be promoted as well as thier health.
